title: For Sale:  Streamlight Twin-Task Flashlight  (new)
postcontent:
Streamlight Twin-Task flashlight

“New”, unopened in sealed plastic clamshell packaging

I bought several of these as Christmas presents in 2003, and this is one that wasn’t given away.

Back in my day, “tactical” flashlights used a high-power xenon bulb.  They are bright, but went through batteries quickly.  And this was back when the 123A batteries were not common, and a lot more expensive.  

The Streamlight Twin-Task gave the user the option of using a xenon light when a bright light was needed, or switching into LED mode when power conservation was important.  It was a good idea, and I carried one for years, but the 100+ lumen LED flashlights of today have made it kind of obsolete, at least as a primary light.    

But they’re still as good today as they were back then, and are perfect as spares to keep around (say, in the glove compartment), which is what I do with mine.  This model has been discontinued by the manufacturer, but they’re still available on Amazon for nearly $50 (for the titanium version, see below).

This is made from aluminium, and feels very solid in the hand.  Try hitting somebody on the head with one of today's plastic flash lights, and you'll appreciate the difference.  Now get off of my lawn.

note:  the batteries that are included are nearing the end of, if not past, their expected shelf life.  I have no idea if they work or not, because the package is sealed.

title: For Sale:  The Factory 22" inch barrel All Original, Matching Bolt,Remington Model 30 Express Deluxe 30-06
postcontent:
Remington Model 30 Express Deluxe 30-06 Serial #29312. All Original, Matching Bolt, The Bolt still has most all of it's Blue on it. Deluxe Checkered Walnut Stock ! The Factory 22" inch barrel has a Mint Bore with strong rifling. This Rifle is as new as I've had it... It has a Great, Tight action. Long extractor. Buckhorn rear sights. Banded front sight with brass bead. Even the Remington marked checkered buttplate has all the blue with only the minimal wear from human-hands over the last Century ! It's Never been drilled and tapped and has all Vivid markings. There is One small blemish in the curved portion of the stocks finish on top of wrist. It has the Factory Sling Swivel Studs. This is in Extroadinary condition for the Most commonly used caliber in a 30 Express with the deluxe checkering. Other than someone having one out there that's new in the Box this is as good as it gets.My price is firm, so if you don't quite understand why, then please read my diatribe below………. I see it as 99.9% ,…. But just to play it safe I'll call it 99 1/2% $1,650 

As I cleaned the MINT Bore I thought to myself; The last time I had a Remington 30 Express, Deluxe 30-06 caliber that was All Original and in this Minty of condition was 30 or 40 years ago. I recalled seeing them "This Good", on occasion back when there was no Gunlist Magazine. And Only the Shotgun News magazine was available. That was in the early 1970's. Later on in the Early 1980's I only saw a few more ( = They were Ususally on a Gun-Dealers Display-Table, along with a lot of other Great Remingtons in Hopes of winning the Best Display at the GunShow. ). 
I'm not sure when I actually owned one of these Remington 30 Express Deluxe Checkered Rifles in this condition that was all original and had this amount of Blue still on the Bolt and didn't have a Peep-sight or something else; Or even that wasn't Tapped on the Receiver for that matter; But I will have to say that it was somewhere back in perhaps the late 1980's Era. I suppose My Point is that it would take a Long Long time to find another that was this GREAT ! And in All Original condition.
